The current state of Highguard Settings and Features is an utterly confusing mess.

The Game seemingly targets a very competitive audience and then abandons that very audience.

It is an absolute sweat fest. 3v3 with punishing respawns and base raiding means communication and team work is brutally important.
So this is NOT for a casual solo que audience.
Which is 100% fine. Many other games target this audience.
But then it's catastrophically missing features that a competitive audience would need and be interested in.

No text chat, no scoreboard, can't ping on the Map, mini compass without degree numbers, No U.I Settings at all, forced motion blur on equipment, A sens slider from hell (you can't enter numbers, only move the slider. the sens range is completely outdated. It goes from 0 to 10 and 1 is 20cm/360 on 800DPI, so at higher DPI's it becomes unusable. The ADS sens has some obtuse ratio. I think it's 1:3 but am i correct ? who knows) No hold for crouch, no toggle for ads,  no analytical tools whatsoever (no stats, Map preview, relevant post match info), no anonymous and streamer mode, no input selector for your microphone.

And these are just the things i am remembering after yesterday. I didn't even keep a list while playing and i usually don't even play ranked.

This is NOT a post about the gameplay or performance or anything else. I am NOT trashing the game as a whole. I actually think people are dismissing it way too early and it got some really incredible foundations, with some sick gameplay.

This post is only about the utter confusion i have about the seeming focus on a specific audience in it's broad strokes and then a completely lack of attention to that audience in other important aspects.
